    <string name="help_title">Help &amp; About</string>
    <string name="help_faq">Frequently asked</string>
    <string name="help_faq_q_sync">Where are my entries stored?</string>
    <string name="help_faq_a_sync">Your entries sync securely to your account in the cloud, so they follow you to any device where you sign in.</string>
    <string name="help_faq_q_photos">Why don\'t my photos show on another device?</string>
    <string name="help_faq_a_photos">Photos are saved on the device you added them from. Connect Google Drive in Settings, or use Backup to file, to carry photos across devices.</string>
    <string name="help_faq_q_backup">How do I back up everything?</string>
    <string name="help_faq_a_backup">Settings → Backup &amp; Restore lets you export all entries and photos to a single .zip file you can re-import anytime.</string>
    <string name="help_faq_q_lock">Can I lock the app?</string>
    <string name="help_faq_a_lock">Yes — turn on App Lock from the menu or Settings to require your fingerprint, face, or screen lock to open Macaco.</string>
    <string name="help_faq_q_billing">How do I cancel or get a refund?</string>
    <string name="help_faq_a_billing">Subscriptions and purchases are billed by Google Play. Open Subscription to manage your plan, or go to Play Store → Payments &amp; subscriptions to cancel. For refunds, use Play Store → order history within 48 hours, or contact us.</string>
